00:23:11,401 --> 00:23:16,600
* AND EVERY DAY WAS SMASHING 

455
00:23:16,633 --> 00:23:18,067
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

456
00:23:19,800 --> 00:23:21,567
DEB! WHAT HAPPENED?

457
00:23:21,601 --> 00:23:23,500
HALEY CAME BY
AND TOLD ME THAT THE --

458
00:23:23,534 --> 00:23:25,733
HALEY. [ LAUGHS ]

459
00:23:25,766 --> 00:23:26,766
I KNEW THAT LITTLE BITCH

460
00:23:26,800 --> 00:23:28,200
COULDN'T KEEP
HER BIG MOUTH SHUT.

461
00:23:30,133 --> 00:23:33,000
I NEED THE GUN
FOR PROTECTION, KAREN.

462
00:23:33,700 --> 00:23:35,700
GUN?

463
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:39,567
TELL ME YOU DIDN'T SHOOT OUT
THE WINDOW WITH CUSTOMERS.

464
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:42,567
YOU COULD HAVE KILLED SOMEONE
OTHER THAN YOUR EX-HUSBAND.

465
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:43,967
WHAT THE HELL IS WRONG
WITH YOU?

466
00:23:44,001 --> 00:23:45,400
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

467
00:23:45,900 --> 00:23:47,368
GIVE ME THE GUN.

468
00:23:47,401 --> 00:23:49,301
[ CHUCKLES ]
I CAN'T.

469
00:23:49,334 --> 00:23:52,334
DEB, I'M NOT PLAYING GAMES
WITH YOUR WACKY ASS.

470
00:23:52,000 --> 00:23:54,566
GIVE ME THE DAMN GUN!

471
00:24:01,533 --> 00:24:02,533
FINE.

472
00:24:09,733 --> 00:24:12,332
HUH. OKAY, NOW I GET IT.
HOW LONG?

473
00:24:12,366 --> 00:24:13,432
IT'S NOT WHAT YOU THINK.

474
00:24:13,466 --> 00:24:14,966
REALLY?
BECAUSE YOU KNOW WHAT I THINK?

475
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:16,599
I THINK YOU'RE A RECOVERING
ADDICT

476
00:24:16,633 --> 00:24:18,733
WHO'S RETURNED TO HER FORMER
LIFE OF POPPING PILLS

477
00:24:18,766 --> 00:24:20,499
AND BRANDISHING FIREARMS!

478
00:24:20,533 --> 00:24:22,266
I JUST HAD A LITTLE SLIP.

479
00:24:22,299 --> 00:24:26,566
IT'S NOT A LITTLE SLIP!
LITTLE SLIPS HAPPEN.

480
00:24:26,599 --> 00:24:29,099
BUT GETTING WASTED
AND SHOOTING UP THE CAFé

481
00:24:29,132 --> 00:24:32,566
DURING THE NOON RUSH
IS NOT A LITTLE SLIP!

482
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:35,700
DEB.

483
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:39,966
YOU NEED TO GET BACK
INTO REHAB.

484
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:42,600
OH.

485
00:24:42,634 --> 00:24:43,966
OR WHAT?

486
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:46,367
OR I WILL DISSOLVE
OUR PARTNERSHIP.

487
00:24:49,066 --> 00:24:49,866
KAREN --

488
00:24:49,700 --> 00:24:52,700
I WILL NOT HAVE
A GUN-TOTING JUNKIE

489
00:24:52,733 --> 00:24:55,366
DESTROY A 17-YEAR-OLD
BUSINESS.

490
00:24:59,600 --> 00:25:01,533
FINE.

491
00:25:01,566 --> 00:25:05,433
YOU CAN HAVE
YOUR LITTLE CAFé.

492
00:25:05,466 --> 00:25:07,133
I QUIT.

493
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:15,934
DEB.

494
00:25:25,535 --> 00:25:27,401
IT'S AN ALTOID.

495
00:25:34,568 --> 00:25:36,434
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

496
00:25:36,468 --> 00:25:38,601
HEY.

497
00:25:38,635 --> 00:25:40,201
YOU OKAY?

498
00:25:40,234 --> 00:25:42,101
YOU SOUNDED A LITTLE CRYPTIC
WHEN YOU CALLED.

499
00:25:42,134 --> 00:25:45,067
YEAH. YEAH.

500
00:25:45,101 --> 00:25:48,201
LOOK, UH, I GUESS THERE'S NO
EASY WAY TO DO THIS,

501
00:25:48,234 --> 00:25:49,767
SO I'M JUST GONNA DO IT.

502
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:52,568
I NEED TO KNOW WHAT HAPPENED
AT THE BRIDGE.

503
00:25:52,800 --> 00:25:56,100
OKAY, BUT YOU SAW A LOT MORE
THAN I DID.

504
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:57,600
I'M NOT SURE ABOUT THAT.

505
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:04,333
LOOK, I SWAM INTO THE CAR,
AND I GOT TRAPPED.

506
00:26:04,367 --> 00:26:07,200
I PANICKED, ALL RIGHT?
I DIDN'T SAVE ANYBODY.

507
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:09,567
AS A MATTER OF FACT,
SOMEBODY SAVED ME.

508
00:26:12,100 --> 00:26:13,600
IT WAS YOU, WASN'T IT?

509
00:26:13,500 --> 00:26:15,467
OH, NATHAN, I WISH IT WAS,
BUT IT WASN'T.

510
00:26:15,500 --> 00:26:16,799
IT HAD TO BE.

511
00:26:16,833 --> 00:26:18,766
LOOK, I WAS TRAPPED
IN THAT CAR, OKAY?

512
00:26:18,799 --> 00:26:20,833
I RAN OUT OF AIR,
AND MY LUNGS GAVE OUT.

513
00:26:20,866 --> 00:26:23,567
NOW, UNLESS WE'RE BOTH DEAD
RIGHT NOW --
NATE, NATE.

514
00:26:23,599 --> 00:26:26,066
LOOK, PEOPLE BLACK OUT
ALL THE TIME IN SITUATIONS

515
00:26:26,100 --> 00:26:29,467
OF, LIKE, CRISIS OR TERROR
OR HIGH-STRESS SITUATIONS.

516
00:26:29,500 --> 00:26:32,066
YOU KNOW, IT'S SOME KIND OF
AN ADRENALINE OVERLOAD.

517
00:26:32,100 --> 00:26:34,732
BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN THAT YOU
DIDN'T SOMEHOW PULL COOPER

518
00:26:34,766 --> 00:26:35,933
AND RACHEL FROM THAT CAR,

519
00:26:35,966 --> 00:26:38,799
EVEN IF YOU DON'T REMEMBER
DOING IT.

520
00:26:38,833 --> 00:26:42,300
THERE WAS NO ONE ELSE THERE,
NATHAN.

521
00:26:42,800 --> 00:26:45,034
IT WAS JUST US.

522
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:48,600
WHAT IF I SAW SOMEONE
IN THE CAR?

523
00:26:48,500 --> 00:26:49,734
YOU MEAN RACHEL AND COOPER?

524
00:26:49,767 --> 00:26:51,201
NO, SOMEONE ELSE.

525
00:26:51,234 --> 00:26:53,567
[ CHUCKLES ] WHO?

526
00:27:00,667 --> 00:27:03,101
KEITH.

527
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:13,000
??

528
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:18,000
YOU GETTING
YOUR GAME FACE ON?

529
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:19,701
[ Laughing ] NO.

530
00:27:19,734 --> 00:27:22,100
WORKING ON YOUR
BROOKE DAVIS MOJO?

531
00:27:23,300 --> 00:27:25,833
I WAS THINKING ABOUT NATHAN.

532
00:27:25,866 --> 00:27:28,367
HE TOLD ME SAW KEITH
IN THE RIVER.

533
00:27:28,400 --> 00:27:31,000
HE SAYS HE WAS TRAPPED
IN THE LIMO,

534
00:27:31,033 --> 00:27:32,467
AND KEITH SAVED HIM.

535
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:35,067
WOW.

536
00:27:35,100 --> 00:27:37,733
KEITH, HUH?

537
00:27:37,767 --> 00:27:39,333
WHAT'D YOU SAY?

538
00:27:39,366 --> 00:27:42,067
KEITH'S DEAD, PEYTON.

539
00:27:45,100 --> 00:27:47,700
IT'S UNBELIEVABLE HOW MUCH
OUR LIVES HAVE CHANGED

540
00:27:47,733 --> 00:27:49,033
SINCE FRESHMAN YEAR.

541
00:27:49,067 --> 00:27:51,900
YEAH.
IT'S ALL GONNA END SOON, TOO.

542
00:27:51,933 --> 00:27:55,200
OR BEGIN.

543
00:27:57,134 --> 00:27:58,634
YOU KNOW
I USED TO WATCH YOU?

544
00:27:58,800 --> 00:28:00,333
WHEN?

545
00:28:00,366 --> 00:28:04,599
OH, FRESHMAN YEAR,
SOPHOMORE YEAR,

546
00:28:04,633 --> 00:28:07,399
BOTH SUMMERS ACTUALLY.
STOP IT.

547
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,699
WHAT DID YOU WATCH?

548
00:28:08,732 --> 00:28:10,300
YOUR LEGS, MOSTLY.

549
00:28:10,333 --> 00:28:12,433
WHAT?!
NO, I'M SERIOUS.

550
00:28:12,467 --> 00:28:14,767
YOU KNOW, FROM UP CLOSE,
THEY'RE A LITTLE CHICKEN-Y.

551
00:28:14,900 --> 00:28:16,067
SHUT UP!

552
00:28:16,101 --> 00:28:19,167
FROM WHERE I WAS HIDING,
THEY WERE PRETTY AWESOME.

553
00:28:19,201 --> 00:28:21,601
[ CHUCKLES ]

554
00:28:21,634 --> 00:28:23,267
I'M NOT SURE
THAT'S A COMPLIMENT.

555
00:28:23,301 --> 00:28:25,434
OH, IT IS. TRUST ME.

556
00:28:27,368 --> 00:28:30,934
I THINK IT SUCKS THAT YOUR
BROTHER HUNG UP ON YOU, PEYTON.

557
00:28:30,967 --> 00:28:32,634
[ SIGHS ] YEAH.

558
00:28:32,668 --> 00:28:35,034
I GET IT, THOUGH --
YOU KNOW,

559
00:28:35,067 --> 00:28:37,468
THE FEAR
OF LETTING PEOPLE IN,

560
00:28:37,501 --> 00:28:39,368
GETTING CLOSE TO SOMEBODY

561
00:28:39,401 --> 00:28:42,034
AND THEN IT JUST
NOT WORKING OUT.

562
00:28:45,735 --> 00:28:50,234
ANYWAY,
UM, ALMOST TIME FOR BROOKE.

563
00:28:50,267 --> 00:28:52,000
ARE YOU READY?

564
00:28:52,034 --> 00:28:53,900
YOU KNOW,
I'VE BEEN THINKING.

565
00:28:53,934 --> 00:28:55,835
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
GO INSTEAD?

566
00:28:55,867 --> 00:28:57,835
YOU KNOW,
PATCH THINGS UP WITH HER.

567
00:28:57,867 --> 00:29:01,368
YOU GUYS HAVE A LIFELONG
FRIENDSHIP THAT'S AT STAKE HERE.

568
00:29:01,401 --> 00:29:04,835
YEAH.
BUT YOU <i>LOVE</i> HER.

569
00:29:04,867 --> 00:29:06,701
[ LAUGHS ]

570
00:29:07,600 --> 00:29:10,199
I DO.

571
00:29:10,700 --> 00:29:12,400
WELL,
YOU SAID IT YOURSELF.

572
00:29:12,433 --> 00:29:13,999
YOU CAN'T HELP
WHO YOU LOVE.

573
00:29:14,033 --> 00:29:16,633
SO THANK YOU
FOR THINKING OF ME,

574
00:29:16,667 --> 00:29:20,099
BUT THIS IS MY BIRTHDAY PRESENT
FOR BROOKE.

575
00:29:20,133 --> 00:29:22,600
ARE YOU SURE?

576
00:29:22,633 --> 00:29:26,366
YEAH. GO AHEAD.
I'LL WAIT.

577
00:29:32,466 --> 00:29:34,199
I'll wait.

578
00:29:39,400 --> 00:29:41,500
YOU THINK
YOUR MOM'S A SPY?

579
00:29:41,533 --> 00:29:43,533
OR A PIMP MAYBE?

580
00:29:43,500 --> 00:29:44,600
[ CHUCKLES ] WHAT?

581
00:29:44,634 --> 00:29:47,134
SHE'S GOT A GUN.

582
00:29:47,168 --> 00:29:48,801
YEAH.
SHE'S PACKING HEAT.

583
00:29:48,834 --> 00:29:50,168
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

584
00:29:50,201 --> 00:29:52,201
YOUR MOM BROUGHT A GUN
INTO THE CAFé TODAY.

585
00:29:52,234 --> 00:29:54,001
OH, AND IT WENT OFF!

586
00:29:54,034 --> 00:29:56,134
WHAT?
WAS ANYBODY HURT?

587
00:29:56,800 --> 00:29:58,032
NO, THANK GOD.

588
00:29:58,900 --> 00:29:59,900
UNBELIEVABLE.

589
00:30:00,100 --> 00:30:01,067
I KNOW.

590
00:30:00,800 --> 00:30:01,767
I'LL TALK TO HER.

591
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:03,967
NOW?
NO.

592
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:05,367
OKAY, BUT SHE'S ACTING
REALLY WEIRD,

593
00:30:05,401 --> 00:30:06,633
AND SHE'S STRAPPED
WITH A NINE.

594
00:30:06,666 --> 00:30:08,000
I GET IT, HALES,

595
00:30:08,034 --> 00:30:10,334
BUT THE PLAYOFFS ARE NEXT WEEK,
AND MY MOM'S AN ADULT.

596
00:30:10,367 --> 00:30:12,234
BOTH MY PARENTS ARE,
SUPPOSEDLY.

597
00:30:12,267 --> 00:30:14,234
WHERE ARE YOU GOING THEN?

598
00:30:14,267 --> 00:30:15,933
THE RIVER COURT.

599
00:30:15,967 --> 00:30:17,134
NATHAN, YOUR KNEE'S ALL --

600
00:30:17,167 --> 00:30:18,767
YOUR MOM IS TOTALLY
FREAKING OUT!

601
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:20,067
I'M THE KID, HALES.

602
00:30:20,100 --> 00:30:21,767
I'M SICK OF DEALING
WITH MY PARENTS' PROBLEMS.

603
00:30:21,800 --> 00:30:23,700
IF IT'S NOT MY DAD
WITH A RESTRAINING ORDER,

604
00:30:23,733 --> 00:30:25,733
IT'S MY MOM WITH A GLOCK.
THEY'RE UNBELIEVABLE.

605
00:30:25,767 --> 00:30:28,900
MY ONE SAVING GRACE,
MY ONE WAY OUT

606
00:30:28,933 --> 00:30:31,700
IS THAT IF I PLAY HALFWAY DECENT
IN THESE PLAYOFFS,

607
00:30:33,801 --> 00:30:36,600
AND GET THE HELL AWAY
FROM BOTH OF THOSE LUNATICS.

608
00:30:40,268 --> 00:30:42,901
SHOULD MY MOM HAVE A GUN?
NO.

609
00:30:42,934 --> 00:30:45,367
BUT AM I GONNA LET HER STUPIDITY
OR ANYTHING ELSE

610
00:30:45,400 --> 00:30:47,034
STAND IN THE WAY
OF MY DREAMS?

611
00:30:47,067 --> 00:30:48,567
NOT A CHANCE.

612
00:30:49,734 --> 00:30:51,001
SEE YOU.

613
00:30:51,034 --> 00:30:52,034
BYE.

614
00:31:01,134 --> 00:31:04,201
KNOCK, KNOCK.

615
00:31:04,234 --> 00:31:06,867
DAN,
YOU CAN'T KEEP DOING THIS.

616
00:31:06,901 --> 00:31:08,534
DOING WHAT?

617
00:31:08,567 --> 00:31:11,134
[ SIGHS ]

618
00:31:10,700 --> 00:31:11,932
COMING AROUND LIKE THIS.

619
00:31:11,965 --> 00:31:14,633
LOOK, I KNOW YOU SAID THAT YOU
INTEND ON BEING THERE

620
00:31:14,666 --> 00:31:16,032
FOR ME WITH THIS PREGNANCY,

621
00:31:16,066 --> 00:31:18,366
BUT THE TRUTH IS, DAN,
YOU ARE NOT THAT GUY.

622
00:31:18,399 --> 00:31:20,799
YOU WERE NOT THAT GUY
THE FIRST TIME WITH LUCAS,

623
00:31:20,100 --> 00:31:22,200
AND YOU'RE NEVER GONNA BE
THAT GUY.

624
00:31:23,500 --> 00:31:25,433
YOU HAVE TO KNOW THAT.

625
00:31:39,500 --> 00:31:42,633
THAT'S LUCAS' CRIB.

626
00:31:42,666 --> 00:31:45,433
DAN, I --
I DID IT MYSELF.

627
00:31:45,900 --> 00:31:48,067
I HOPE YOU LIKE IT.

628
00:32:12,700 --> 00:32:14,767
OKAY,
I BRING YOU TO THIS CLUB.

629
00:32:14,800 --> 00:32:18,300
I FILL YOUR KITSCHY BUT HIDEOUS
SPICE GIRL MUG WITH ALCOHOL,

630
00:32:18,333 --> 00:32:19,933
AND YOU HAVEN'T TOUCHED IT.

631
00:32:19,966 --> 00:32:22,033
IS THIS HOW YOU SPEND
ALL YOUR BIRTHDAYS?

632
00:32:22,066 --> 00:32:24,333
ACTUALLY, NO. I USUALLY
SPEND THEM WITH PEYTON,

633
00:32:24,367 --> 00:32:25,767
BUT NOT THIS YEAR.

634
00:32:25,800 --> 00:32:27,999
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH THAT?
I MISSED A COUPLE THINGS

635
00:32:28,033 --> 00:32:30,166
WHEN I WAS HANGING OUT
AT THE BOTTOM OF THE RIVER.

636
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,700
PEYTON LIKES LUCAS.

637
00:32:31,734 --> 00:32:34,533
DID SHE TRY TO SLEEP WITH HIM?
'CAUSE I DID THAT, TOO.

638
00:32:34,567 --> 00:32:35,533
SHE KISSED HIM.

639
00:32:35,567 --> 00:32:37,266
THE DAY
OF THE SCHOOL SHOOTING,

640
00:32:37,300 --> 00:32:39,266
SHE KISSED HIM
IN THE LIBRARY.

641
00:32:41,800 --> 00:32:43,234
WELL, BY DEFAULT,

642
00:32:43,267 --> 00:32:45,767
IF YOU'RE ABOUT TO DIE,
OR AT LEAST BLEEDING TO DEATH,

643
00:32:45,800 --> 00:32:47,600
I THINK YOU GET A FREE
KISSING PASS.

644
00:32:47,633 --> 00:32:49,833
WHAT ELSE DID SHE DO?

645
00:32:49,867 --> 00:32:52,767
WELL, SHE HAD THE NERVE
TO SAY SHE'D BACK OFF

646
00:32:52,800 --> 00:32:54,100
 <i>IF</i> I LOVED HIM.

647
00:32:54,400 --> 00:32:55,633
CAN YOU BELIEVE THAT?

648
00:32:55,667 --> 00:32:57,999
SHE WANTED ME TO DECLARE MY LOVE
FOR MY OWN BOYFRIEND.

649
00:32:58,033 --> 00:32:59,266
WHY DIDN'T YOU?

650
00:33:02,100 --> 00:33:03,800
OKAY,
LET ME GET THIS STRAIGHT.

651
00:33:03,833 --> 00:33:05,599
YOU DON'T HAVE FEELINGS
FOR LUCAS ANYMORE.

652
00:33:05,633 --> 00:33:07,100
PEYTON DOES.

653
00:33:07,133 --> 00:33:09,733
YET SHE'S WILLING TO HIDE THOSE
FEELINGS IF YOU ASK HER TO.

654
00:33:11,700 --> 00:33:15,134
SOUNDS LIKE A PRETTY GREAT
FRIEND TO ME.

655
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:15,367
Woman: YEAH!

656
00:33:21,800 --> 00:33:25,634
CHECK IT OUT.
YOUR BIRTHDAY PRESENT'S HERE.

657
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:29,000
WELL, AT LEAST ONE OF THEM.
YOU PICK.

658
00:33:28,300 --> 00:33:30,333
ISN'T IT A LITTLE SOON
FOR YOU?

659
00:33:30,367 --> 00:33:32,300
IS COOPER'S TUX
EVEN DRY YET?

660
00:33:33,700 --> 00:33:35,700
COOPER'S GONE, BROOKE.

661
00:33:35,900 --> 00:33:37,900
SO I'M USING YOUR BIRTHDAY
AS AN EXCUSE

662
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:39,499
TO DROWN MY SORROWS IN ALCOHOL
AND BOY.

663
00:33:40,200 --> 00:33:42,500
RACHEL, A ONE-NIGHTER
IS JUST GONNA MAKE IT WORSE.

664
00:33:42,533 --> 00:33:44,166
TOMORROW,
IT'LL MAKE IT WORSE,

665
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:47,600
BUT TONIGHT, TRUST ME,
IT'LL MAKE IT MUCH BETTER.

666
00:33:47,634 --> 00:33:48,899
SO WHICH ONE DO YOU WANT?

667
00:33:51,500 --> 00:33:52,933
I CAN'T.

668
00:33:53,400 --> 00:33:54,900
SUIT YOURSELF.

669
00:33:54,900 --> 00:33:56,666
DON'T WAIT UP.

670
00:33:58,965 --> 00:34:01,699
* DON'T BE AFRAID
TO TELL ME THAT *

671
00:34:01,733 --> 00:34:03,599
* OH! 

672
00:34:03,633 --> 00:34:07,266
* DON'T BE AFRAID
TO TELL ME THAT *

673
00:34:07,800 --> 00:34:09,767
COME ON, BROOKE.

674
00:34:18,500 --> 00:34:20,266
I'M SORRY, LUKE.

675
00:34:20,300 --> 00:34:22,066
I REALLY THOUGHT
SHE WAS GONNA SHOW.

676
00:34:22,099 --> 00:34:23,233
BUT LOOK AT IT THIS WAY.

677
00:34:23,266 --> 00:34:25,133
SHE DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE GONNA BE HERE,

678
00:34:25,166 --> 00:34:27,133
SO THERE'S STILL HOPE
FOR THE TWO OF YOU,

679
00:34:27,166 --> 00:34:30,533
JUST NOT SO MUCH
FOR ME AND HER.

680
00:34:44,099 --> 00:34:47,466
HERE.
I STOLE THIS FOR YOU.

681
00:34:47,500 --> 00:34:50,833
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

682
00:34:50,867 --> 00:34:52,567
AH.

683
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:54,166
[ LAUGHS ]

684
00:34:54,199 --> 00:34:55,733
IT SMELLS GOOD.

685
00:34:55,767 --> 00:34:56,934
[ GIGGLES ]

686
00:34:56,967 --> 00:34:58,400
TRY IT ON.

687
00:34:58,433 --> 00:35:00,034
[ LAUGHS ]

688
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:10,667
BEST BIRTHDAY EVER.

689
00:35:13,900 --> 00:35:16,900
WHEN I WAS 12.

690
00:35:16,933 --> 00:35:18,933
MY MOM AND KEITH
SURPRISED ME

691
00:35:18,967 --> 00:35:21,533
WITH TICKETS
TO THE DUKE-CAROLINA GAME.

692
00:35:21,566 --> 00:35:24,700
OH, NO, WE DROVE UP,
MADE A WEEKEND OUT OF IT.

693
00:35:24,733 --> 00:35:26,666
IT WAS COOL BECAUSE
IT WAS THE FIRST TIME

694
00:35:26,700 --> 00:35:28,500
WE WERE EVER A REAL FAMILY.

695
00:35:30,300 --> 00:35:33,733
AND I'D GIVE ANYTHING
TO HAVE THAT BACK.

696
00:35:34,299 --> 00:35:35,833
YOU?

697
00:35:35,867 --> 00:35:39,566
MY EIGHTH BIRTHDAY.
MY MOM WAS STILL ALIVE.

698
00:35:39,600 --> 00:35:43,333
THAT'S THE LAST TIME
WE WERE A REAL FAMILY.

699
00:35:44,900 --> 00:35:48,000
I'D GIVE ANYTHING
TO HAVE THAT BACK.

700
00:35:52,132 --> 00:35:54,900
YOU WANT ME TO DRIVE YOU
BY RACHEL'S?

701
00:35:54,933 --> 00:35:56,500
MAYBE BROOKE'S THERE.

702
00:35:56,533 --> 00:35:59,266
Lucas: <i>THERE ARE MOMENTS</i>
 <i>IN OUR LIVES</i>

703
00:35:59,299 --> 00:36:01,800
 <i>WHEN WE FIND OURSELVES</i>
 <i>AT A CROSSROADS.</i>

704
00:36:01,833 --> 00:36:03,566
NO.

705
00:36:03,600 --> 00:36:05,999
THAT'S OKAY.

706
00:36:06,032 --> 00:36:08,532
WOULD YOU DROP ME
BY THE RIVER COURT?

707
00:36:08,700 --> 00:36:10,800
IT'S WHERE I DO
MY BEST HEALING.

708
00:36:11,399 --> 00:36:14,066
SURE.

709
00:36:14,099 --> 00:36:16,266
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

710
00:36:27,500 --> 00:36:29,166
 <i>THERE ARE MOMENTS IN OUR LIVES</i>

711
00:36:29,500 --> 00:36:31,901
 <i>WHEN WE FIND OURSELVES</i>
 <i>AT A CROSSROADS.</i>

712
00:36:35,800 --> 00:36:40,434
 <i>AFRAID, CONFUSED,</i>
 <i>WITHOUT A ROAD MAP.</i>

713
00:36:46,900 --> 00:36:49,199
 <i>THE CHOICES WE MAKE</i>
 <i>IN THOSE MOMENTS</i>

714
00:36:49,233 --> 00:36:51,333
 <i>CAN DEFINE THE REST</i>
 <i>OF OUR DAYS.</i>

715
00:36:53,100 --> 00:36:57,100
* GET OUT OF BED 

716
00:36:57,300 --> 00:37:01,833
* PICK UP THE PHONE 

717
00:37:01,867 --> 00:37:08,467
* TIME TO TELL THE PRESS 

718
00:37:08,501 --> 00:37:12,000
 <i>OF COURSE, WHEN FACED</i>
 <i>WITH THE UNKNOWN...</i>

719
00:37:12,034 --> 00:37:13,534
* SAY TO MYSELF 

720
00:37:12,900 --> 00:37:16,533
 <i>...MOST OF US PREFER</i>
 <i>TO TURN AROUND AND GO BACK.</i>

721
00:37:18,400 --> 00:37:20,234
DOING A LITTLE SCOUTING?

722
00:37:22,200 --> 00:37:25,300
I'M PUTTING HIM
ON THE TEAM.

723
00:37:25,334 --> 00:37:27,901
REALLY?

724
00:37:27,934 --> 00:37:31,200
WELL, THAT'S GREAT, COACH.
WHAT MADE YOU DECIDE?

725
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:34,400
YOU DID.

726
00:37:34,600 --> 00:37:36,600
NOT LONG AGO,

727
00:37:36,500 --> 00:37:40,667
I FOUND A KID
OUT ON THAT VERY SAME COURT.

728
00:37:41,800 --> 00:37:45,300
IF THAT YOUNG MAN TURNS OUT
TO BE THE KIND OF PLAYER

729
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:48,633
AND PERSON THAT SCRAWNY KID
TURNED OUT TO BE

730
00:37:48,667 --> 00:37:52,400
[LAUGHS]
IT'S A NO-BRAINER.

731
00:37:52,433 --> 00:37:56,867
* GET OUT OF BED 

732
00:37:56,900 --> 00:38:01,400
* COME OUT AND SING 

733
00:38:01,433 --> 00:38:06,400
* BLUE SKIES AHEAD 

734
00:38:06,433 --> 00:38:09,733
* THE MAN WHO TOLD EVERYTHING 

735
00:38:09,767 --> 00:38:11,700
YOU JUST BECAME A RAVEN.

736
00:38:11,733 --> 00:38:13,099
[ LAUGHS ]

737
00:38:14,500 --> 00:38:15,700
 <i>BUT ONCE IN A WHILE,</i>

738
00:38:15,733 --> 00:38:17,934
 <i>PEOPLE PUSH ON</i>
 <i>TO SOMETHING BETTER...</i>

739
00:38:17,967 --> 00:38:21,566
* LIKE I'M LOSING MY HEAD 

740
00:38:26,401 --> 00:38:29,800
 <i>...SOMETHING FOUND JUST BEYOND</i>
 <i>THE PAIN OF GOING IT ALONE...</i>

741
00:38:30,400 --> 00:38:34,634
* LIVES HAVE BEEN WRECKED 

742
00:38:34,667 --> 00:38:37,400
* AND I PICKED UP MY CHECK 

743
00:38:37,433 --> 00:38:38,500
ARE YOU PEYTON?

744
00:38:43,600 --> 00:38:45,300
I'M DEREK.

745
00:38:49,533 --> 00:38:52,333
I GUESS I'M YOUR BROTHER.

746
00:38:52,366 --> 00:38:54,866
 <i>...AND JUST BEYOND</i>
 <i>THE BRAVERY AND COURAGE</i>

747
00:38:54,500 --> 00:38:56,434
 <i>IT TAKES TO LET SOMEONE IN...</i>

748
00:38:56,467 --> 00:39:04,101
* I'M GONNA GET OUT
OF HE-E-E-RE *

749
00:39:04,900 --> 00:39:06,966
 <i>...OR TO GIVE SOMEONE</i>
 <i>A SECOND CHANCE.</i>

750
00:39:06,999 --> 00:39:10,133
* I'M GONNA SAIL 

751
00:39:10,166 --> 00:39:12,767
* GET OUT OF BED 

752
00:39:12,800 --> 00:39:16,667
 <i>SOMETHING BEYOND THE QUIET</i>
 <i>PERSISTENCE OF A DREAM.</i>

753
00:39:20,033 --> 00:39:24,700
* BLUE SKIES AHEAD 

754
00:39:26,300 --> 00:39:29,800
HAPPY BIRTHDAY,
YOU BORING OLD SHREW.

755
00:39:30,999 --> 00:39:33,900
YOU SAID, "DON'T WAIT UP."

756
00:39:33,934 --> 00:39:35,567
AND YOU CALL THIS LATE?

757
00:39:35,600 --> 00:39:37,033
I WASN'T INTO IT.

758
00:39:37,500 --> 00:39:41,734
THE BOYS IN TREE HILL ARE
SO BORING COMPARED TO COOPER.

759
00:39:41,767 --> 00:39:45,634
ISN'T THERE ANYBODY OUR AGE
YOU THINK YOU COULD FALL FOR?

760
00:39:51,500 --> 00:39:54,000
MAYBE.

761
00:40:02,500 --> 00:40:06,700
I FOUND YOUR BALL AT HOME.

762
00:40:06,734 --> 00:40:08,866
I WAS KIND OF HOPING
YOU WOULD.

763
00:40:15,800 --> 00:40:18,167
I NEED YOU TO TALK TO ME.

764
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:22,167
HALEY.

765
00:40:22,201 --> 00:40:25,701
I'M NOT TRYING
TO SHUT YOU OUT, OKAY?

766
00:40:25,900 --> 00:40:30,566
I JUST DON'T UNDERSTAND IT
ENOUGH TO LET YOU IN YET.

767
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:34,167
WHATEVER IT IS,

768
00:40:34,201 --> 00:40:36,201
WE'RE GONNA GET THROUGH IT
TOGETHER.

769
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:39,733
I'M RIGHT HERE.

770
00:40:39,767 --> 00:40:41,568
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

771
00:40:44,100 --> 00:40:46,100
 <i>BECAUSE IT'S ONLY</i>
 <i>WHEN YOU'RE TESTED</i>

772
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:49,200
 <i>THAT YOU TRULY DISCOVER</i>
 <i>WHO YOU ARE.</i>

773
00:40:49,233 --> 00:40:58,433
* EVERYTHI-I-I-NG 

774
00:40:58,600 --> 00:41:00,799
 <i>AND IT'S ONLY</i>
 <i>WHEN YOU'RE TESTED</i>

775
00:41:00,832 --> 00:41:03,133
 <i>THAT YOU DISCOVER</i>
 <i>WHO YOU CAN BE.</i>

776
00:41:06,899 --> 00:41:08,966
HEY.

777
00:41:08,999 --> 00:41:11,765
I'M SORRY
ABOUT YOUR BIRTHDAY.

778
00:41:12,300 --> 00:41:14,667
DID ANYTHING MEMORABLE
HAPPEN?

779
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:18,700
YEAH, ONE THING.

780
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:20,733
 <i>THE PERSON YOU WANT TO BE</i>
 <i>DOES EXIST,</i>

781
00:41:20,766 --> 00:41:23,701
 <i>SOMEWHERE ON THE OTHER SIDE</i>
 <i>OF HARD WORK</i>

782
00:41:23,733 --> 00:41:25,400
 <i>AND FAITH AND BELIEF...</i>

783
00:41:30,400 --> 00:41:36,400
 <i>...AND BEYOND HEARTACHE</i>
 <i>AND FEAR OF WHAT LIES AHEAD.</i>

784
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:48,000
